<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="221" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,497,186,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
Description (
<figureCitation box="[354,482,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Figs 2A–B</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Thinly encrusting sponge (≈ 
<quantity box="[835,926,186,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.52" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" unit="cm" value="15.2">15.2 cm</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[926,934,186,200]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">2</superScript>
), less than 
<quantity box="[1067,1133,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
thick (
<quantity box="[1214,1379,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" unit="mm" value="0.5" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.2">0.2 to 0.8 mm</quantity>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Consistency very soft and fragile. Surface smooth, with visible oval to circular areolated porefields (3.4 x 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" unit="cm" value="1.3">1.3 cm</quantity>
largest and smallest diameters) and subectosomal canals, oscula visible 
<emphasis box="[998,1067,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">in situ</emphasis>
(≈ 
<quantity box="[1106,1237,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" unit="cm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.4 cm</quantity>
). (
<figureCitation box="[1264,1352,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Color brownish beige in life (
<emphasis box="[412,481,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">in situ</emphasis>
) and beige transparent when preserved in ethanol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,330,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
Skeleton (
<figureCitation box="[317,446,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Figs 2C–D</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Ectosomal skeleton with ectosomal strongyles to subtylotes forming longitudinal bundles from surface to substrate (
<figureCitation box="[497,586,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Subectosomal and choanosomal skeletons overlapping, composed of typical hymedesmioid structure, consisting of a basal layer of spongin, with acanthostyles I and II erect on the substrate (
<figureCitation box="[159,248,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Isochelae, sigmas and microstrongyles (
<figureCitation box="[716,804,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) appear scattered in the sponge, and some acanthostyles I lay parallel to, or flat on the substrate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,552,510,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
Spicules (
<figureCitation box="[312,441,510,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Figs 2E–N</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation box="[454,542,510,537]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="8.[151,239,612,638]" captionText="TABLE 1. Hymedesmia (Hymedesmia) spp. from Peru. Measurements (in µm) of the spicules (n = 30; unless stated otherwise in parentheses), length x thickness [as minimum– mean–maximum (± standard deviation)], distribution and bathymetry (in meters). Roman numerals correspond to size categories of acanthostyles.Abbreviations: Tor. (tornotes), Str. (strongyles), Sbty. (subtylotes), Tyl. (tyles), Sty. (styles), Ac. (arcuate chelae), Sig. (sigmas) and Mstr. (microstrongyles)." pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Table 1</tableCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Ectosomal diactines: strongyles to subtylotes, smooth, straight (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1371,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
) with rounded ends (
<figureCitation box="[317,445,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2 H –I</figureCitation>
), 129– 
<emphasis box="[521,584,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">153.1</emphasis>
–187 (± 16.3) × 3.6– 
<emphasis box="[817,852,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">4.5</emphasis>
–5.2 (± 0.4) × 3.8–5.0 µm (tyle, N = 3) (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1425,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Figs 2G–I</figureCitation>
). Choanosomal acanthostyles I (
<figureCitation box="[491,578,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
): larger, apex tapering gradually, acerate tip, base occasionally with a more or less distinct swelling; shaft straight to slightly curved, spines slightly curved or conical and spread from base to mid shaft, 158– 
<emphasis box="[276,339,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">206.2</emphasis>
–270 (± 31.9) × 5.4– 
<emphasis box="[570,605,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">8.3</emphasis>
–11.1 (± 1.9) µm. Choanosomal acanthostyles II (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1246,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
).: straight, tapering gradually, acerate tip and round base, spines spread all along the spicule, curved, those at the base bent as hooks, 76– 
<emphasis box="[193,242,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">83.8</emphasis>
–96 (± 5.0) × 4.9– 
<emphasis box="[443,478,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">6.1</emphasis>
–7.9 (± 0.7) µm. Arcuate isochelae (
<figureCitation box="[878,1012,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Figs 2M–N</figureCitation>
): one free spatulate ala and two lateral alae semi-fused with the shaft; shaft characteristically curved, bow-shaped, 17– 
<emphasis box="[1045,1094,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">19.1</emphasis>
–21 (± 1.1) × 2.4– 
<emphasis box="[1300,1335,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">3.7</emphasis>
–4.8 µm. Sigmas (
<figureCitation box="[249,330,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Fig. 2J</figureCitation>
): C shape, tips straight and acerate, 27– 
<emphasis box="[774,823,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">29.4</emphasis>
–33 (± 2.2) × 2.9– 
<emphasis box="[1027,1062,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">3.2</emphasis>
–3.9 (± 0.3) µm. Microstrongyles (
<figureCitation box="[159,287,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[192,1395,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hymedesmia (H.) santarositae sp. nov. A–B, live specimen (MNRJ 12843); C, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; D, microstrongyles in ground section; E, choanosomal acanthostyle I; F, choanosomal acanthostyle II; G, ectosomal tornote; H–I, details of G; J, sigma; K–L, microstrongyles; M–N, isochelae. Scale bars:A, approx. 5 cm; B, 1 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 100 µm; E–G, 100 µm; H–I, 20 µm; J–N, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831767/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Figs 2K–L</figureCitation>
): smooth, curved and robust, rounded ends, 24– 
<emphasis box="[822,871,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">28.6</emphasis>
–34 (± 2.7) × 2.3– 
<emphasis box="[1075,1110,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">3.4</emphasis>
–4.6 (± 0.5) µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="221" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,871,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Ecology.</emphasis>
Specimen collected from a nearly vertical rocky substratum, at 
<quantity box="[1048,1084,871,897]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" unit="m" value="8.0">8m</quantity>
depth. Growing over tubes of polychaetes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,932,942,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1077]" box="[199,932,942,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,942,968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[601,649,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingCountry box="[752,792,943,969]" name="Iceland" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Isla</collectingCountry>
Santa Rosa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1308,979,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1077]" box="[199,1308,979,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,979,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name, “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2022" box="[566,703,979,1004]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="santarositae">
<emphasis box="[566,703,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">santarositae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to its 
<typeStatus box="[856,904,979,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">type</typeStatus>
locality also called 
<collectingCountry box="[1128,1168,979,1005]" name="Iceland" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Isla</collectingCountry>
Santa Rosa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="221" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu, 2022" authorityName="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,667,1015,1041]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="santarositae" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Hymedesmia">
<emphasis box="[323,468,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Hymedesmia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[485,513,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[530,667,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">santarositae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[676,767,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[676,767,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1020,1254,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis box="[1020,1165,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Hymedesmia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(table 2) by the presence of microstrongyles as microscleres, in addition to arcuate chelae and sigmas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
